parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.
Of another nation, a foreigner. From allos and genos; foreign, i.e. Not a Jew.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To turn back, return. From hupo and strepho; to turn under, i.e. To return.
To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.
From the base of dokeo; glory, in a wide application.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
